with (at least) the following in the commit message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This closes #1188&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit 0f570b0c620df9f1145ed8c3e31363560f3835e1&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Ismael Juma &amp;lt;ismael@juma.me.uk&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2016-04-05T09:07:56Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3510&quot; title=&quot;OffsetIndex thread safety&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-3510&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-3510&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; OffsetIndex thread safety&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Make all fields accessed outside of a lock volatile&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Only allow mutation within the class&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Remove unnecessary `AtomicInteger` since mutation always happens inside a lock&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


